24/03/2003
LJUBLJANA, Slovenia -- The Greek embassy in Slovenia congratulated the country on the outcome of its referendum Sunday (23 March), approving EU and NATO accession.
In a televised address released immediately after the first exit polls, an embassy representative vowed to support the accession deadlines.
Greece holds the EU's rotating presidency.
Preliminary results show 89 per cent favoured EU membership, compared to 66 per cent for NATO entry.
(STA, TV Slovenija, HINA - 23/03/03)
